  "prompt": "Why did Pepper Potts leave Tony Stark in Captain America: Civil War? Why wasn\u2019t she in the film?",
  "response": "Pepper Potts, played by Gwyneth Paltrow, was not featured in \"Captain America: Civil War\" because her character was written to have taken a break from her relationship with Tony Stark. In the film, Tony Stark (Iron Man) mentions to Steve Rogers (Captain America) that he and Pepper are \"taking a break\" due to the stresses and complications arising from Stark's life as Iron Man and his involvement in the Avengers. This plot point was used to add to the emotional and personal stakes for Stark's character during the events of the movie.\n\nFrom a behind-the-scenes perspective, another reason for her absence could be related to scheduling conflicts or contract negotiations with Gwyneth Paltrow. However, the specific details regarding her absence in \"Captain America: Civil War\" were not officially disclosed.",
